    "body": "Removed the [Process exited] message that appeared in terminals with a finished process from the buffer contents and added it to the status line. However, to do that, it was necessary to expose struct terminal in src/nvim/terminal.h\r\n\r\nfixes: #14986\r\n\r\nBREAKING CHANGE: the Terminal type definition is not being supplied by \"nvim/types_defs.h\" anymore. It is being supplied by \"nvim/terminal.h\".",
    "closed_at": null,
    "comment_data": [],
    "comment_regular_data": [
        {
            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": ">Removed the [Process exited] message that appeared in terminals with a finished process from the buffer contents and added it to the status line.\r\n\r\nWhat happens if a user has a custom `'statusline'` set?\r\n\r\n>However, to do that, it was necessary to expose struct terminal in src/nvim/terminal.h\r\n\r\nThis shouldn't be necessary. The struct definition is \"private\" to the implementation. You can add new APIs if callers outside of the terminal implementation need to manipulate the internal data structure.\r\n\r\n",
