            "body": "> What happens if a user has a custom 'statusline' set?\r\n\r\nIn the cases that the user has a custom statusline set, it doesn't change anything. In those instances, the logic that is controlling the custom statusline isn't known.\r\n\r\n> This shouldn't be necessary. The struct definition is \"private\" to the implementation. You can add new APIs if callers outside of the terminal implementation need to manipulate the internal data structure.\r\n\r\nOkay, I will add an API instead of exposing the internal data structure",
