        {
            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "> Instead of altering the nvim API, wouldn't it be better to add the exit code as a statusline item (e.g. %e) for users with a custom statusline?\r\n\r\nThat seems like a hack, to avoid the work that is actually needed, which is that channel info should be available even after a channel/job exits--something that's generally needed for various purposes. Whereas, adding some internal \"pass around the exit code... just so the _statusline_ can show it\" logic is just yet another hack, and not an isolated one.\r\n\r\nAnother approach would be to allow job handlers to be defined on _existing_ jobs: https://github.com/neovim/neovim/issues/5023 . Then the exit-code could be captured by a Lua callback which sets the statusline or whatever.",
