        {
            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "> A `nvim_buf_get_termchan(handle): id` will also be necessary since there currently aren't any ways to obtain the id of the terminal's channel.\r\n\r\nAs @zeertzjq hinted, the buffer-local `&channel` option gives the terminal channel-id.",
